bringing the Gap: College Man at 42
By Steve Otto
Poker»faced and suffering, a
gathering of Englishmen stated
up at their renewable mayor,
Thomas Middleton, who had
come 10 give a speech at the
cold, daily medication ceremony of a newlyrbuilt schoolhouse. At one corner of the
structure, someone had shipped
out the date: 1651.
Middleton’s frequency didn’t
star in a n y hearts that
day, but he entered one line
that struck a note of import
tality in the townspeople's beds
dining ears: “A man is never
too old to learn!"
Evidence that this magic is
just as true today as it was
in 1651 can be found at the
Grinnell College physics workshop.
There, meeting out from behind a network of multicolored
wires and tubes, 'is the face of
Charles pierce. Pierce, at 42,
is one of the few men of the
age who has successfully
bridges the generation gap
without the aid of a heard or
long hair. His formula: “Become a student!” And as a
Grinnell College student, he
extends six hours of class a
week and holds down a full“
time job as the college‘s physics technician. With a blair for
reading schematics programs
and explanation notes from
college processors, he fits right
in.
Born and raised near Brooklyn, Iowa, Pierce comes from
a “family of large families” as
he puts it He has five sisters
and one brother, “None of us
started very far from home,”
he says. “My brother, who
lives further away than the
rest of us, besides in selling."
Pierce’s mother has 29 grandchildren, and seven of them
belong to Pierce. His children
are garcia, 15, there, 14, Steven, 12, sydney, 10, Jon, 6,
Curtis, 3, and Jodi, almost 2.
As if seven children women’t
enough, he went out and got
himself a little league baseball
team which he coaches in the
summer. Even seven children,
the little league baseball team,
and 20 years away irbm school
have not trained his energy
and desire to learn. He extends
an astronomy class and a math
class right along with students
22 years his junior.
He has an insatiable authority, which has undoubtedly been
an asset in his rather unusual
line of work. Specifically, his
work involves setting up various experiments and concentrations for physics classes,
keeping the physics department’ vast store of indicate
equipment in proper working
order, and even building a few
integrate pieces of physics
equipment himself when processors require it He recently
completed a spectroscope, an
optical device used for forming
light special for study,
If you are saying to yourself, “That type of Work sounds
as if it might get complicated
at times," you're right. For
someone who has had no for
may education in electronics or
physics —— and who didn’t know
a methods ray tube from an
era when he first started —
Pierce gives a good account of
himself.
Catch him lifetime
conversation with a college
physics professor, and you’ll
have a tough time trying to
decide which gentleman is
supposed to have a string of
letters after his name. The
press rely on him for all types
of general information and ads
vice, His excellent background
as a mechanism and mechanic
combined with What he has
learned in the past two years
as a physics technician make
him a good reference source.
But he scores when referred
to as “really, quite a bright
fellow." “You can learn a lot,”
he notes, “by osmosis e simply according what you see.”
If that's the case, his mind
is a spouse for physics facts,
After graduation from high
school, he spent six years in
the Navy, worked another six
